  • creating a table for the first goal
data_clean <- function(csv){
  library(reshape2)
  library(plyr)
  library(ggplot2)
  
  data <- read.csv(csv)
  data <- data[,-1]
  data$user_id <- as.integer(as.character(data$user_id))
  data$timestamp <- as.numeric(as.POSIXct(data$timestamp))
  data <- data[data$user_id %in% data[data$event_type == "AccountCreated", 1], ]
  data <- dcast(data, user_id ~ event_type, value.var = "timestamp", fun = min)
  
  data$check <- data$AccountCreated + 7*24*60*60 # add a within 1 week time check
  
  #replace Inf with time fillers, more than 1 week
  data[,3][data[,3] == Inf] <- max(data[,3][data[,3] != Inf]) + 8*24*60*60
  data[,4][data[,4] == Inf] <- max(data[,4][data[,4] != Inf]) + 8*24*60*60
  data[,5][data[,5] == Inf] <- max(data[,5][data[,5] != Inf]) + 8*24*60*60
  data[,6][data[,6] == Inf] <- max(data[,6][data[,6] != Inf]) + 8*24*60*60
  
  #create a T/F count table for event type
  data1 <- data.frame("user_id" = data[,1], 
                      deleted = ifelse(data[,3] <= data$check, 1, 0), 
                      m_created = ifelse(data[,4] <= data$check, 1, 0),
                      suggested = ifelse(data[,5] <= data$check, 1, 0),
                      accepted = ifelse(data[,6] <= data$check, 1, 0),
                      "time_check" = data$check
  )
  data1 <- data1[data1$deleted == 0, c(-2)] # remove users who cancelled with 1 week
  data1$time_check <- as.POSIXct(data1$time_check, origin = '1970-01-01')
  data1 <- data1[order(data1$time_check), ]
  data1 <- data.frame(data1[,-5], time_check = as.Date(as.character(data1$time_check)))
  
  # convert into daily event count
  data2 <- ldply(lapply(split(data1[,c(2:4)], data1$time_check),
                        function(x){
                          data.frame(sum(x[,1]), sum(x[,2]), sum(x[,3]))}),
                 rbind)
  colnames(data2) <- c("date", "Manually Created", "Name Suggested", "Suggestion Accepted")
  
  data2$new_user <- 
  (data2$`Manually Created`+data2$`Suggestion Accepted`)/(data2[,2]+data2[,3]+data2[,4])
  
  return(data2)

}

table <- data_clean("assignment06_3m_on.csv")

  • plotting: first week name suggestion
plotting <- function(data){
  library(ggplot2)
  data <- melt(data, id = "date", variable.name = "event_type", value.name = "count")
  data$date <- as.Date(as.character(data$date))
  graph1 <- 
    ggplot(data[data$event_type != "Suggestion Accepted", ], aes(fill = factor(event_type,
                                  levels = c("Manually Created","Name Suggested")),
                   y = count, x = date)) +
    geom_bar(position = "fill", stat = "identity") + labs(fill = "Event Type") +
     ggtitle("First week name suggestion")
  return(graph1)  
}

plotting(table)

  • First Week Activation
plotting1 <- function(data){
  library(ggplot2)
  data$new_user <- 
  (data$`Manually Created`+data$`Suggestion Accepted`)/(data[,2]+data[,3]+data[,4])
  
  data <- melt(data, id = "date", variable.name = "event_type", value.name = "count")
  data$date <- as.Date(as.character(data$date))

  graph1 <-
    ggplot(data[data$event_type == "new_user" ,], aes(group = event_type, y = count, x = date)) + geom_line(aes(color = event_type)) + geom_point(aes(color = event_type)) + 
    ggtitle("First Week Activation")
  return(graph1)
  }

plotting1(table)
